We first calculate the average total assets. The initial total assets (from 2023-12-31) are 13,000,000.00 and the ending total assets (from 2024-01-28) are 16,213,861.65. Their average is:

  Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 16,213,861.65) / 2  
                = 29,213,861.65 / 2  
                ≈ 14,606,930.83

Next, from the income statement the net profit is 1,103,190.60. The Return on Assets (ROA) is computed by dividing net profit by the average total assets, then converting to a percentage:

  ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%  
     = (1,103,190.60 / 14,606,930.83) × 100%  
     ≈ 0.0755 × 100%  
     ≈ 7.55%

Thus, the Return on Assets (ROA) is approximately 7.55%.
